Joseph J. TAYLOR, Appellant, v. CALMAR STEAMSHIP CORPORATION, Appellee. No. 13338. United States Court of Appeals Fourth Circuit. Argued Dec. 2, 1969. Decided Jan. 5, 1970. Bernard J. Sevel, Baltimore, Md. (Russell Jay Bennett, Baltimore, Md., on brief), for appellant. David R. Owen, Baltimore, Md. (Semines, Bowen & Semmes, Baltimore, Md., on brief), for appellee.

Before BRYAN, CRAVEN and BUTZ-NER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

The findings of fact are not clearly erroneous. To those findings the district judge applied correct principles of law. Since no other questions are presented, the decision below will be

Affirmed.
